#week-title("One", "The Principle of Cohobation")

=== Core Teaching

The spagyric is completed when what has been separated is reunited — purified by
separation, and then conjoined at a higher level. This is the operation called
*cohobation*: the pouring of the extracted essence back over the calcined salt,
so that the salt absorbs the spirit and soul of its own plant.

The process is methodical. The calcined salt is placed in a flask. The liquid
essence (Mercury and Sulphur combined) is poured over it, and the flask is sealed
and placed in gentle warmth for digestion. Over days and weeks, the salt absorbs
the essence.

#doctrine[
  _"When the liquid has cleared — when the salt will absorb no more — the process
  may be repeated with fresh essence to increase potency. Each repetition raises
  the vibration of the resulting preparation."_
  #align(right)[— TTAO curriculum]
]

=== Topics This Week

- The definition and purpose of cohobation
- Preparation for the reunion: pre-heated flask and warm salt
- Duration of the first cohobation: two weeks minimum
- Identifying saturation: when the liquid no longer darkens

#inner-work[
  *The Triple Point*

  Thomas Vaughan teaches that the *Anima Mundi* (the World Soul) is the animating
  spirit within the *Spiritus Mundi*. When the three principles are genuinely
  cohobated, what is produced is a localised intensification of the World Soul.

  Reflect on this: What would it mean for your Sulphur (nature), Mercury
  (intelligence), and Salt (body) to be genuinely conjoined at a higher level
  than they currently are? Record your thoughts in your journal.
]

